# Reap rotated jellyfin logs older than 14d. Serilog rolls log files by
# date (log_<date>.log) inside the container but never deletes old ones,
# so the host /var/log/jellyfin bind-mount would grow forever. ~14d is
# mtime-only: the tilde tells tmpfiles to ignore atime, so a file that gets
# re-read (not rewritten) still ages out on its real write time.
#
# Type Path              Mode UID GID Age   Argument
e      /var/log/jellyfin -    -   -   ~14d  -
